Sentencas: Solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) are promising electrochemical energy conversion devices owing to their high power generation efficiency and environmentally benign operation.
Titulo: Micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cell based on a porous yttria-stabilized zirconia support

Sentencas: Micro-tubular SOFCs, which have diameters ranging from a few millimeters to the sub-millimeter scale, offer several advantages over competing SOFCs such as high volumetric power density, good endurance against thermal cycling, and flexible sealing between fuel and oxidant streams.
Titulo: Micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cell based on a porous yttria-stabilized zirconia support

Sentencas: Herein, we successfully realized a novel micro-tubular SOFC design based on a porous yttria-stabilized zirconia (YSZ) support using multi-step dip coating and co-sintering methods.
Titulo: Micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cell based on a porous yttria-stabilized zirconia support

Sentencas: The micro-tubular SOFC consisted of Ni-YSZ, YSZ, and strontium-doped lanthanum manganite (LSM)-YSZ as the anode, electrolyte, and cathode, respectively.
Titulo: Micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cell based on a porous yttria-stabilized zirconia support

Sentencas: In addition, to facilitate current collection from the anode and cathode, Ni and LSM were applied as an anode current collector and cathode current collector, respectively.
Titulo: Micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cell based on a porous yttria-stabilized zirconia support

Sentencas: Micro-crystalline cellulose was selected as a pore former to achieve better shrinkage behavior of the YSZ support so that the electrolyte layer could be densified at a co-sintering temperature of 1300 degrees C.
Titulo: Micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cell based on a porous yttria-stabilized zirconia support

Sentencas: The developed micro-tubular design showed a promising electrochemical performance with maximum power densities of 525, 442, and 354 mW cm(-2) at 850, 800, and 750 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cell based on a porous yttria-stabilized zirconia support
